III. Release Note Numbering
===========================
Info over numbering of release notes IE 1.04.12.023:

First number => Device Version
  1. Edgecon V1
  2. 
  3. 
  4. 
  5. Modberry (https://github.com/bynacon/meta-modberry.git)
  6. 
  7. 
  8. 
  9. 

Second number => Main release number
third number => Sub versioning number 
fourth number => Patch number

IIII. Release Note Edgecon
==========================

--- Release 1.00.04 ---
First commit standard configuration of Raspberrypi CM4.
Without any configuration of mender. Most of hardware is running.

- WIFI is running
- Bluethoot is running

--- Release 1.01.05 ---
Image with mender configurations.

- Connecting to Mender-Server
- Troubleshooting is running
- File transfere is running
- Device configuration is running
- Enable port forwording

--- Release 1.01.10 ---
Add docker, docker-compose an accesspointmode for communication with wifi devices, i.e. ESP32, ESP8266...

--- Release 1.01.14 ---
Hardware new functions
- HDMI
- uart2
- uart4
- spi1-3cs
- spi4-1cs
- i2c0
- i2c1

--- Release 1.02.21 ---
Hardware new functions
- Fix USB2 Host problems (Local)
- Add access point mode via wlan0_ap and change wlan0 to wlan0_sta. Now we can operate access point mode and station mode in parallel.
- Add a standard WiFi connection to a network via wlan0_sta (Without security "plain text")
- Disable pci at uboot. uboot running in loop, while pci_xhci has a bug at line 481
- Add networkinterface eth1 to eth3 over symlink at systemd
Hardware disable
- Detect disk with size and mount it / add a SD Card with release 1.04.12.023
Configuration fix
- Prepare configuration with JSON-file


--- Release 1.04.12.031 ---
Hardware new functions
- sd0 (sdcard), creat a overlay for sd0 and add a mountingpoint
- Change SPI1 to SPI4 if SPI1 is a auxilery SPI who had only SPI-Mode 0 and 2.
Software
- Add "C" Programmingtools
- Add "Python3" Programmigntools 
Configuration fix
- Prepare examplefiles for configuration with JSON-file
#TEMP - Config display rotation over cmdline.txt => fbcon=rotate:1 "this change only the cmdline after boot process" Disable splash, psplash and change kernel output to console
#TEMP - set all Users wihtout a password


To Do:
#TODO - Networkconfiguration bridge and members of bridge
#TODO - Create C Code to comunicate with DI/DO at SPI

IIII. Release Note Modberry
===========================

--- Release 5.01.01.004 ---
First commit standard configuration of Raspberrypi CM4 Modberry.

- WIFI is running
- Bluethoot is running
- I2C0 is running
  - RTC is running
